        <p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
        <p n="1">Third year of the victorious king Nandivikramavarman.</p>
        <p n="2-4">
               Three hundred goats that the honourable Tikaittiṟal, who had the temple of Viṣṇu <supplied reason="subaudible">named after</supplied> Tikaittiṟal built in Kiḷiñelūr in the Oymānāṭu, gave for a glorious lamp
and two fields, east of the glorious temple, that he also <supplied reason="explanation">
            <foreign>ivarē</foreign>
          </supplied> gave for the glorious food <supplied reason="subaudible">are given</supplied> tax-free <supplied reason="explanation">
            <foreign>iṟaiyili</foreign>
            <note>According to the summary in <ptr target="bib:Mahalingam1988_01"/>, this applies only to the land donation. This makes sense but goes agaisnt the syntax of the sentence.</note>
          </supplied>.

            </p>
        <p n="4">The florious feet of those who protect this pious deed are on my head.</p>
